verbs.description: withhold (third-person singular simple present withholds, present participle withholding, simple past withheld, past participle withheld or (rare, archaic) withholden)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To keep (a physical object that one has obtained) to oneself rather than giving it back to its owner.
examples: The bank withheld her credit card.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To keep (information, assent etc) to oneself rather than revealing it.
